OL,7,F"This was a long, complex and
OL,8,Fchallenging investigation for a team
OL,9,Fof officers and staff who had to work
OL,10,Fthrough the most harrowing evidence to
OL,11,Fbring those responsible for these
OL,12,Fdespicable crimes to justice."
OL,14,FMary Glasgow, chief executive at
OL,15,FChildren First said: "No sentence will
OL,16,Fever reflect the extreme cruelty and
OL,17,Fhorrifying abuse that three children
OL,18,Fendured for so long. The depths of
OL,19,Ftheir suffering will be unimaginable
OL,20,Fto most people in Scotland, but none
OL,21,Fof us should turn away from it.
